nodes.bodyText:
Just for reminder:
org.polarsys.capella.core.commands.preferences.service.AbstractPreferencesInitializer are inconsistent and not working properly.
putInt If the InstanceScope contains a value, at restart the default value will contains the previous instance value, not the one given in parameter. It will never set only the default value. always in instance scope.
putBoolean and putString used in 
  
    
      capella/core/plugins/org.polarsys.capella.core.model.preferences/src/org/polarsys/capella/core/model/preferences/DeletePreferences.java
    
    
         Line 35
      in
      6ef8e89
    
    
    
    

        
          
           putBoolean(IDeletePreferences.PREFERENCE_CONFIRM_DELETE, true, DefaultScope.class); 
        
    
  

 do nothing if DefaultScope.
If ProjectScope, like used in initializer, as there is never a selected project at startup, its also weird.
